      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Pierre John Huss (1903-1966) was a journalist and author.  During World War II he was chief International News Service (INS) correspondent in Berlin and is the author of <emph render="italic">Heil! And Farewell: The Foe We Face</emph> (1942).</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p><emph render="bold">Historic Radiograms from Pierre Huss</emph> consists of a scrapbook containing radiograms about the American campaign in Sicily and Italy during World War II from war correspondent Pierre Huss, presented to Harry A. King for the purchase of war bonds during Press-Radio Day on 25 September 1943 in Syracuse, N.Y.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
